{"id":842,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":205,"title":"Cam8 - Test 4 - Part 1","subtitle":"Hotel Waiter Job Inquiry","level":"B1","parts":81,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam8-test-4-part-1.842/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/0-ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Hello, West Bay Hotel. Can I help you?\nOh, good morning.\nI'm ringing about your advertisement in the Evening Gazette.\nIs that the one for temporary staff?\nThat's right.\nYes.\nI'm afraid the person who's dealing with that isn't in today,\nbut I can give you the main details if you like.\nYes, please.\nCould you tell me what kind of staff you are looking for?\nWe're looking for waiters at the moment.\nThere was one post for a cook, but that's already been taken.\nOh right.\nWhat are the hours of work?\nThere are two different shifts -\nthere's a day shift from 7 to 2\nand a late shift from 4 till 11.\nAnd can people choose which one they want to do?\nNot normally, because everyone would choose the day shift I suppose.\nYou alternate from one week to another.\nOkay. I'm just writing all this down.\nWhat about time off?\nYou get one day off\nand I think you can negotiate which one you want,\nit's more or less up to you.\nBut it has to be the same one every week.\nDo you know what the rates of pay are?\nYes, I've got them here.\nYou get £5.50 an hour,\nand that includes a break.\nDo I have to go home to eat or...\nYou don't have to.\nYou can get a meal in the hotel if you want to,\nand there's no charge for it so you might as well.\nOh good.\nYes, so let's see.\nI'd get er..., 221, no, no, £231 a week?\nYou'd also get tips.\nOur guests tend to be quite generous.\nErm, is there a uniform?\nWhat about clothes?\nYes, I forgot to mention that.\nYou need to wear a white shirt, just a plain one,\nand dark trousers.\nYou know, not green or anything like that.\nAnd we don't supply those.\nThat's okay, I've got trousers,\nI'd just have to buy a couple of shirts.\nWhat about anything else?\nDo I need a waistcoat or anything?\nYou have to wear a jacket, but the hotel lends you that.\nI see.\nOne last thing - I don't know what the starting date is.\nJust a minute, I think it's sometime around the end of June.\nYes, the 28th, in time for the summer.\nThat's great. I'm available from the 10th.\nOh good.\nWell, if you can call again you need to speak to the Service Manager.\nHer name's Jane Urwin,\nthat's URWIN,\nand she'll probably arrange to meet you.\nOkay.\nAnd when's the best time to ring?\nCould you call tomorrow?\nShe usually starts checking the rooms at midday,\nso before then if you can, so she'll have more time to chat.\nI'll just give you her number because she's got a direct line.\nThanks.\nIt's 832009.\n823009?\n832.\nOh, okay.\nYes, I'll do that.\nAnd by the way, she will ask you for a reference,\nso you might like to be thinking about that.\nYou know, just someone who knows you and can vouch for you.\nYes, no problem.\nWell, thanks very much for your help.\nYou're welcome.\nBye.\nBye.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:11","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Hello, West Bay Hotel. Can I help you?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/1.mp3","time_start":0.39,"time_end":3.66},{"position":2,"content":"Oh, good morning.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/2.mp3","time_start":3.66,"time_end":4.86},{"position":3,"content":"I'm ringing about your advertisement in the Evening Gazette.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/3.mp3","time_start":4.86,"time_end":8.13},{"position":4,"content":"Is that the one for temporary staff?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/4.mp3","time_start":8.13,"time_end":10.61},{"position":5,"content":"That's right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/5.mp3","time_start":10.61,"time_end":11.46},{"position":6,"content":"Yes.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/6.mp3","time_start":11.65,"time_end":12.83},{"position":7,"content":"I'm afraid the person who's dealing with that isn't in today,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/7.mp3","time_start":12.83,"time_end":16.46},{"position":8,"content":"but I can give you the main details if you like.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/8.mp3","time_start":16.46,"time_end":19.27},{"position":9,"content":"Yes, please.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/9.mp3","time_start":19.27,"time_end":20.58},{"position":10,"content":"Could you tell me what kind of staff you are looking for?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/10.mp3","time_start":20.58,"time_end":23.63},{"position":11,"content":"We're looking for waiters at the moment.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/11.mp3","time_start":23.63,"time_end":26.25},{"position":12,"content":"There was one post for a cook, but that's already been taken.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-4-part-1-2023-07-27-13-01-28/12.mp3","time_start":26.25,"time_end":29.66},{"position":13,"content":"Oh right.","audio_url":"htt